            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1107">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Potsdam)/8–945</note>
                <head>No. 1107<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Executive Secretary of the Central
                        Secretariat</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_YCW1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Yost</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1107fn1">Printed from the ribbon copy, which is
                        unsigned. For the minutes of the discussions summarized in this memorandum,
                        see <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_55">pp. 55</ref>, <ref target="#pg_174">174</ref>–<ref target="#pg_175">175</ref>, <ref target="#pg_323">323</ref>, <ref target="#pg_464">464</ref>–<ref target="#pg_465">465</ref>, <ref target="#pg_482">482</ref>, <ref target="#pg_484">484</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extracts<note n="2" xml:id="d1107fn2">For the other
                            sections of this memorandum, see <ref target="#d738">documents Nos.
                                738</ref> and <ref target="#d1093">1093</ref>.</note>]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-09">August 9,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin Conference</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Italy</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Soviet Policy</hi>
                </p>
                <p>. . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>On two occasions the Soviets presented proposals in regard to the imposition of
                    reparations on Italy.<note n="3" xml:id="d1107fn3">
                        <ref target="#d1099">Documents Nos. 1099</ref> and <ref target="#d1104">1104</ref>.</note> The United States and Britain refused to agree
                    except in the case of delivery of capital equipment from <gloss target="#t_War1">war</gloss> industries having no peacetime utility. No decision was taken
                    on this matter.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">British Policy</hi>
                </p>
                <p>… On reparations he<note n="4" xml:id="d1107fn4">i. e., <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName>.</note> said that the British did
                    not wish them for themselves but were thinking of Greece.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>… They<note n="5" xml:id="d1107fn5">i. e., <persName corresp="#p_ACR1">Attlee</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BE3">Bevin</persName>.</note> also strongly supported the United States position
                    on Italian reparations.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
